                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 28, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4787. Your 5045, October 22, 7 p.m. and 5073, October 24, 5 p.m.<note n="12"
                        xml:id="d569fn12">Latter not printed.</note> The War Department has a supply
                    ship ready to sail from Hawaii for Christmas Island October 30. Please request
                    British concurrence in starting immediate construction. You may add, if the
                    question is raised, that we regard any construction there as without prejudice
                    to the general question of sovereignty over the island.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
